    "body": "### Problem\n\n#39891 only fixed the simple case where the fold below the virtual line is at level 1. For nested folds, `foldcolumn` does not draw anything next to the virtual line.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n-- line 1\n-- line 2\n-- line 3\n-- line 4\n\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"ns\")\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, { virt_lines = { { { \"below line 2\", \"\" } } } })\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 2, 0, { virt_lines_above = true, virt_lines = { { { \"above line 3\", \"\" } } } })\n\nvim.o.foldcolumn = '2'\nvim.cmd(\"1,4fold | 1,4foldopen\")\nvim.cmd(\"3,4fold | 3,4foldopen\")\n```\n\n- `nvim --clean test.lua -c '%lua'`\n\n<img width=\"159\" height=\"146\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6f0dd296-13ca-47b9-b651-1c295c207af3\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`foldcolumn` should continue through the virtual lines:\n\n<img width=\"159\" height=\"146\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4d39e1d2-f646-4029-9ea2-ce6e55a11ee5\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-592+g70792aa6e4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from repo",
